Overview


Goal(s):

This script with using the package ecospat to do a niche comparison between the best fit calling and noncalling models.


Details about files and pipeline:


  1. File information
  • The models in this script were generated in the previous script maxent_models for the 1) calling and the 2) noncalling populations.


  1. File contents
  • List and describe the columns in your input file. If applicable, indicate the type of variable, whether it is a predictor or response, etc.

Extract environmental data

extract the environmental data under the input locality points from the stack of rasters

calling_extract <- cbind(calling_locs, terra::extract(env_stack, calling_locs[,c("Long_m", "Lat_m")]))

noncalling_extract <- cbind(noncalling_locs, terra::extract(env_stack, noncalling_locs[,c("Long_m", "Lat_m")]))


Niche Quantification

## Extract env values to a matrix

## Entire AB/BC area - summary of the total environmental variability
env_df <- values(env_stack)
env_df <- as.data.frame(env_df)
env_df <- na.omit(env_df)

## Within the calling range
call_df <- values(call_stack)
call_df <- as.data.frame(call_df)
call_df <- na.omit(call_df)

## Within the non-calling range
noncall_df <- values(noncall_stack)
noncall_df <- as.data.frame(noncall_df)
noncall_df <- na.omit(noncall_df)


## Generate PCA with env variables and extract scores
pca.env <- dudi.pca(env_df, center = TRUE, scale = TRUE, scannf = FALSE, nf = 2)


## li is the row coordinates (i.e. principal components)
env.scores <- pca.env$li


calling.scores <- suprow(pca.env, data.frame(calling_extract)[, colnames(env_df)])$li

calling.env.scores <- suprow(pca.env, call_df)$li


noncalling.scores <- suprow(pca.env, data.frame(noncalling_extract)[, colnames(env_df)])$li
noncalling.scores <- na.omit(noncalling.scores)

noncalling.env.scores <- suprow(pca.env, noncall_df)$li
noncalling.env.scores <- na.omit(noncalling.env.scores)


Occurrence Density Grids

## in the function ecospat.grid.clim.dyn: 
## 1) envi values for the whole study area, 
## 2) envi values for the background of the species,
## 3) envi values for the occurrences of the species

calling.grid <- ecospat.grid.clim.dyn(env.scores, calling.env.scores, calling.scores)
## Registered S3 methods overwritten by 'adehabitatMA':
##   method                       from
##   print.SpatialPixelsDataFrame sp  
##   print.SpatialPixels          sp
noncalling.grid <- ecospat.grid.clim.dyn(env.scores, noncalling.env.scores, noncalling.scores)


## Niche plot showing the calling density
niche_plot <- ecospat.plot.niche.dyn(calling.grid, noncalling.grid, 
                                     name.axis1 = "PC1",
                                     name.axis2 = "PC2", quant = 0.05, interest=1,
                                     colZ1 = "orange3",
                                     colZ2 =  "skyblue3",
                                     col.stab = "darkblue",
                                     col.exp= "orange",
                                     col.pio = "skyblue2")

## Niche plot showing the Non-calling density
niche_plot <- ecospat.plot.niche.dyn(calling.grid, noncalling.grid, 
                                     name.axis1 = "PC1",
                                     name.axis2 = "PC2", quant = 0.05, interest=2,
                                     colZ1 = "orange3",
                                     colZ2 =  "skyblue3",
                                     col.stab = "darkblue",
                                     col.exp= "orange",
                                     col.pio = "skyblue2")

Calculate Niche overlap value (Schoeners D)

overlap_vals <- ecospat.niche.overlap(noncalling.grid, calling.grid, cor=TRUE)
overlap_vals
## $D
## [1] 0.004974178
## 
## $I
## [1] 0.03450853
## Randomizing the Non-calling
NC_similarity_vals <- ecospat.niche.similarity.test(calling.grid, 
                                         noncalling.grid,
                                         rep = 1000,
                                         intersection = 1,
                                         rand.type = 2, 
                                         overlap.alternative = "higher"
                                         )

## Observed D
NC_D_val <- NC_similarity_vals[["obs"]][["D"]]
NC_pvalue <- NC_similarity_vals[["p.D"]]
NC_D_val
## [1] 0.004974178
NC_pvalue
## [1] 0.3346653
NC_simulation_vals <- NC_similarity_vals[["sim"]]


NC_similarity_vals_plot <- ggplot(NC_simulation_vals, aes(x=D)) +
  geom_histogram(binwidth = 0.002, fill = "#69b3a2", color = "black") +
  geom_vline(aes(xintercept = NC_D_val), color = "red", linetype = "dashed", linewidth = 1) +
  labs(
    title = "Null Distribution of Schoener's D (randomizing Non-calling density)",
    x = "Simulated D values",
    y = "Frequency"
  ) +
  theme_minimal()

NC_similarity_vals_plot

ggsave(plot=NC_similarity_vals_plot, "./similarity_test_NC-randomized.jpeg", dpi = 600)
